{
  "texts": [
    "Experiment 4: comparing LLMs fine-tuned on single datasets versus models fine-tuned on an ensembled dataset The goal of Experiment 4 was to investigate whether fine-tuning LLMs on ensembled datasets from multiple sources outperform LLMs fine-tuned on single-source datasets.",
    "To create the ensembled dataset, we aggregated all data from the five evaluation datasets and then randomly partitioned the ensembled dataset into training, validation, and test sets following the 0.8-0.1-0.1 ratio.",
    "The BERT-based models were fine-tuned on the training and validation sets and evaluated on individual test sets from each evaluation dataset so that the performance is a fair comparison with results from the BERT-based models fine-tuned on individual datasets.",
    "For example, BERT_base_ensemble was fine-tuned on a random set of 80% of all data aggregated from the five evaluation datasets.",
    "It was then evaluated individually on random sets of 10% of each of the five datasets."
  ]
}